  "source_notes": "LMR quotes Chaplin in ''My Autobiography'' (1964), page 14: \"I was born on 16 April 1889, at eight O'clock at night, in East Lane, Walworth. Soon after, we moved to West Square, St George's Road, Lambeth. According to Mother my world was a happy one.\"\\n\\nSy Scholfield notes that 15 April is given in birth notices. For example, ''The Era'' (London), 11 May 1889, page 18, gives this date, born to \"the wife of Charles Chaplin, nee Lily Harley\" (see at left). The biography, ''Chaplin, His Life and Art'' by David Robinson (McGraw-Hill, 1985), page xxiv, quotes Chaplin's birth notice in ''The Magnet'', 11 May 1889, for \"the 15th ultimo,\" i.e. 15 April. There is no entry for Chaplin in the England and Wales Birth Index and no known birth certificate. \\n\\nOther references: born in Smethwick (Birmingham) or Chaplin could be named Thomstein and be born in Fontainebleau, France. Starkman rectified to 16 April 1889 19.40.48 GMT Asc 5Sco17'.\\n",
